data.name: label3.Text
data.value:
- When the checker is selected, it highlights in beige. The possible moves are highlighted in blue, so it is easier for player to choose. - Chechkers can only be moved diagonally. - Multiple pieces can be eaten, and player can also eat it's own checker. - Regular checkers can move only towards the opponents end of the board, and once the end is reached, the checker becomes the king. - The king can move both ways.
- The goal is to eat all the opponents checkers, or to capture him so that he can't make any more moves.
